SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uopacus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Opacus</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Apprentice</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>12/16/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>10:26:48 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/srawczak/opac2.bmp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">AE Snare</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I have died for the last time to stupid AE snare.  Im kiting something and it breaks so i have to recast.  Fizzles 3 times then, lo and behold i am snared too.  Im pised because I have to have 255MR to use one of my spells to full.  Another thing, why is everything in Velious an undercon?  I love having to gate after failing root/snare 5 times and having my DD's do absolutely nothing to a friggin lvl 25 mob.  Snaring yourself sucks!!!</font><P><c><IMG SRC=http://www.geocities.com/srawczak/opacbanner.bmp><c><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#33333><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umysthyl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mysthyl</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Wizard</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>12/17/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>4:52:19 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">not so bad</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">First of all you need to time the spell so if you are kiting past when it wears off recast it BEFORE if does. Secondly NEVER cast this spell when you are in range no matter what your mr, it has a nasty habbit of getting through just at that one point which will get you killed. <br>
