Mysthyl</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/unygex.showPublicProfile?language=EN>nygeX</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Apprentice</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>1/2/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>9:40:23 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re:</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">BoF is probably my favorite spell yet I've read this type of post quite a few times it seems.  I don't think I have ever cast it on myself so maybe it is a lag issue?  I get a good connection with the occasional lag spike but maybe this is your problem.  You know - where a mob is 100 yards away one second and on top of you the next.  Also, if I start casting and it looks like the mob has gotten too close I start running, cancelling the cast.  Now, I have done this hundreds of times.  Maybe you are the type that is willing to take that risk - not me.</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#33333><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udevia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Devia</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC= http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif  BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Apprentice</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>1/3/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>12:55:03 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Re:</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Was just single kiting in DL tonight...managed to BoF myself <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   ya'd think i'd learn. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   happened cause he resisted my first, and came at me.  At any rate, I keep root up now, for that reason.  If BoF is resisted or breaks, root it, and run to the edge of casting range.  Nuke it till root breaks (usually one for me lately) and when it does, BoF will work nicely again.  mob should be far enough away, and you get a nuke or two in in the process.  Im sure there are other, better ways...but i know my stun gets resisted a bit too much right now, so i try not to count on it when i solo.<br>
